[Student "S"]
{NORTH cannot respond with a Negative Double on this hand because he has only three 
\Hs.

Instead he just bids his 4-card Major, 1\S.

SOUTH shows 4-card support with a minimum opener by bidding 2\S and NORTH 
has enough strength to bid game.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:AT532.AJT.987.A8 Q74.K54.Q54.J632 K9.862.AK63.KQ75 J86.Q973.JT2.T94"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1S 2H X pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "6cac296dc73fe834aaec432e999378531ac07c3d73c29eea7d5169999db6f6cd"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/negative_doubles"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST has 15 points, and when South overcalls 2\H in front 
of her she has a perfect Negative Double - showing both of the Minor suits.

EAST doesn't like the Minor suits, but he has stoppers in \Hs, so 
he bids 2NT.

WEST is more than happy to raise to 3NT.}

